    Notes:

    - Though I think a button on the right side of the heading would semantically be more correct (something like "+"), mouse users want to click on the whole heading, so wrapping a link around it is needed (it's href is the container's ID)
    - JAWS announces the headings redundantly when activating them the first time (in browse mode), especially in FF the state is announced as "expanded collapsed".

